<p>As the DC Robotics program grows, however, we figured greater exposure could only help strengthen interest.  With that in mind, this public portion of the site opened up so you&mdash;whoever you may be&mdash;can have some idea who we are and what we're all about.</p>

<p>James Kurtz ('11), the programmer of the pilot DC Robotics team, has been developing web pages since fifth grade and could not resist the opprotunity to use his skills on a site that people actually look at.  He wrote all of the HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, and server scripting to strict standards-compliance and avoided proprietary plugins (like Flash and Silverlight) to minimize browser issues.  If you have a comment on the structure of the site, he'd love to hear from you.  You can send him an email at <a class="_noajax" href="mailto:jamesk@dcrobotics.org?subject=Site Feedback">jamesk@dcrobotics.org</a>. </p>